parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive rusting of the chassis can lead to structural damage, causing the vehicle to become unsafe to drive and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: oil and fuel lines rusted and falling off

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the head gasket can cause the engine to stall, leading to loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
The repeated failure of the fan blower switch can cause the fan to malfunction, leading to overheating and potentially causing engine damage.
The failure of the fan blade can cause damage to the engine compartment and surrounding components, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: shards of fan blade causing damage to the engine compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine hesitation and stumbling can cause loss of power and control, increasing the risk of accidents.
The failure of the exhaust valves can cause engine damage and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: Exhaust valves from cylinders 3 and 6 failed

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the manual transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, slip out of gear, or become stuck in gear, leading to loss of control, accidents, or strandings.
symptoms: Loud whirring sound in fifth gear
third gear popping out while accelerating

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear axle seal can cause the brakes to become soaked in oil, leading to loss of braking power, accidents, or strandings.
symptoms: Seal on rear axle started leaking

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Extensive frame rust can compromise the structural integrity of the vehicle, making it unsafe to operate and increasing the risk of accidents or collapse.
symptoms: Visible rust or corrosion on the frame
or other components; vibrations or unusual noises coming from the rear of the vehicle; sagging or uneven ride height.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Body rust can lead to perforation and compromise the overall safety and reliability of the vehicle, potentially causing airbag deployment issues or other safety concerns.
symptoms: Visible rust or corrosion on the body
or other exterior components; rust holes or perforation; replacement of rusted parts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the master cylinder can cause extended stopping distances, brake failure, and accidents, which can lead to injuries or fatalities.
Brake failure on wet roads can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities due to loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: Vehicle skids when brakes are applied on wet roads
